ZH: 我有一个关于未来的猜想。
EN: I have a guess about the future.

ZH: 他对自己的未来有很多猜想。
EN: He has many guesses about his own future.

ZH: 我们之间的矛盾引发了很多猜想。
EN: The conflict between us sparked many guesses.

ZH: 这个问题的答案要等很久，所以只能猜想一下了。
EN: The answer to this question will take a long time, so we can only guess.

ZH: 她猜想自己会在未来取得更大的成功。
EN: She guesses that she will achieve greater success in the future.

ZH: 我在等待结果的时候产生了各种猜想。
EN: I had all kinds of guesses while waiting for the results.

ZH: 他的猜想最后都被证明是错误的。
EN: His guesses were proven to be wrong in the end.

ZH: 我们不应该凭空猜想，应该等待事实的证实。
EN: We shouldn't guess without evidence, we should wait for the facts.

ZH: 他对这个问题的猜想一直都是错的。
EN: His guesses about this problem have always been wrong.

ZH: 真相往往比我们的猜想更加惊人。
EN: The truth is often more surprising than our guesses.

ZH: 我的猜想并没有得到他的认同。
EN: My guess didn't get his approval.

ZH: 她反复猜想着他的想法。
EN: She kept guessing his thoughts over and over again.

ZH: 在我们找到答案之前，我们只能做猜想。
EN: We can only make guesses until we find the answer.

ZH: 我对这种说法持怀疑态度，我有自己的猜想。
EN: I am skeptical about this statement, I have my own guesses.

ZH: 别对那些空泛的猜想轻信。
EN: Don't trust those vague guesses.

ZH: 没有任何根据的猜想是危险的。
EN: Baseless guesses are dangerous.

ZH: 猜想未来的结果使我感到兴奋。
EN: Guessing the outcome of the future excites me.

ZH: 我的猜想并没有被证实。
EN: My guess has not been confirmed.

ZH: 他猜想这个计划可能会失败。
EN: He guesses that this plan might fail.

ZH: 我一直在为这个问题纠结，无法做出准确的猜想。
EN: I have been struggling with this issue, unable to make accurate guesses.
